OL,3,CSpiking laws to be reformed to send
OL,4,Cclearer message to perpetrators
OL,6,FPlans to modernise spiking laws will
OL,7,Fbe set out in the coming days, the
OL,8,Fgovernment has said.
OL,10,FMinisters have come under pressure to
OL,11,Fmake needle and drink spiking a
OL,12,Fspecific offence, with campaigners and
OL,13,Fopposition parties calling for tougher
OL,14,Faction to protect women.
OL,16,FWhile full details are not yet clear,
OL,17,Fthe Home Office has said it will amend
OL,18,Fthe Criminal Justice Bill and update
OL,19,Fthe Offences Against The Person Act
OL,20,F1861 to make clear that spiking is
OL,21,Fillegal.
